HEADWORD: Overvalue
<hw>O`ver*val"ue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overvalued</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overvaluing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To value
excessively; to rate at too high a price.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To
<xex>overvalue</xex> human power.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Holyday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exceed in value.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>H. Brooke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overveil</ent>⟦br⟧
